article.description: Davauhnte Turner had 18 points and Dallas Watson posted 17 points as St. Peter's narrowly beat Marist 71-68 in overtime in the first round of the Metro Atlantic Conference Tourney on Thursday.
article.headline: Turner lifts St. Peter's over Marist 71-68 in OT
article.linkText: Turner lifts St. Peter's over Marist 71-68 in OT
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Davauhnte Turner had 18 points and Dallas Watson posted 17 points as St. Peter's narrowly beat Marist 71-68 in overtime in the first round of the Metro Atlantic Conference Tourney on Thursday. Quinn Taylor had 11 points for St. Peter's (10-21). KC Ndefo added four blocks. Brian Parker had 22 points for the Red Foxes (12-19). Ryan Funk added 18 points. Aleksandar Dozic had 11 points. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
